a) fork()- creates a new child processor to duplicating calling parent proces.both processes simultaneously in 
separate memory spaces
exec()-replace the current process image with a new program
b)wait()- blocks the parent process until the child process completes execution 
c)System call sequence using fork(), exec(), and wait():
  START 
  pid=fork()
  if pid<0
  print"child process failed"
  pid==0 then 
  print"child process created "
  Else if 
  print"child process running"
  wait()
  THEN 
  print"child process completed"
  print"parent process completed"

  

   
